The paper deals with modeling knowledge acquisition in complex networks, which is a topic that can be approached from various perspectives in computer science. Based on the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper explicitly mentions the use of network models and the influence between researchers. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper involves the development of a multi-agent random walk model. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper touches upon the social aspect of knowledge acquisition. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper deals with the discovery process and memory. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper involves the acquisition and organization of knowledge.
